Beyond compliance, investigate the principles of moral behavior and its effects on people, the community, and the economy. Develop your personal integrity by working through real-world situations and case studies, taking calculated risks, and creating an open culture. Learn the fundamentals of ethical leadership in the workplace and use them to solve practical issues like resource allocation and procurement. This course aims to enable you to become a change agent, with the information and abilities to fight corruption and create a more equitable future, rather than just checking boxes. So come to UTM and unleash your ethical compass by joining the cause!
